<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="420" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="420">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,222,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="420">Biology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Ramil &amp; Vervoort" authorityYear="1992" box="[302,476,223,249]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Bougainvilliidae" genus="Garveia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="8" pageNumber="420" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="nutans">
<emphasis box="[302,476,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="420">Garveia nutans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is frequently found growing on stones, algae, hydroids and other hard substrata in areas with strong tidal currents (
<bibRefCitation author="Schuchert, P." box="[490,672,259,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="420" pagination="195 - 396" refId="ref44822" refString="Schuchert, P. (2007) The European athecate hydroids and their medusa (Hydrozoa, Cnidaria): Filifera Part 2. Revue suisse de Zoologie, 114, 195 - 396. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 80395" type="journal article" year="2007">Schuchert 2007</bibRefCitation>
). Fertile colonies have been found between February and December (
<bibRefCitation author="Schuchert, P." box="[159,339,295,321]" pageId="8" pageNumber="420" pagination="1 - 364" refId="ref44871" refString="Schuchert, P. (2012) North-West European Athecate Hydroids and their Medusae. Synopses of the British Fauna, New Series, 59, 1 - 364." type="journal article" year="2012">Schuchert 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gil, M. &amp; Ramil, F." box="[350,571,295,321]" pageId="8" pageNumber="420" pagination="419 - 444" refId="ref39805" refString="Gil, M. &amp; Ramil, F. (2017 a) Hydrozoans from Mauritanian Deep-Waters. In: Ramos, A., Ramil, F. &amp; Sanz, J. L. (Eds.), Deep sea ecosystems off Mauritania: Researching marine biodiversity and habitats in West African Deep-waters. Springer, Dordrecht, pp. 419 - 444. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 024 - 1023 - 5 _ 11" type="book chapter" year="2017">Gil &amp; Ramil 2017a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,501]" box="[199,831,331,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="420">Our colonies were found with gonophores in November.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="420" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="420">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,366,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="420">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species has a worldwide distribution in boreal and temperate seas (
<bibRefCitation author="Ramil, F. &amp; Vervoort, W." box="[1162,1431,367,393]" pageId="8" pageNumber="420" pagination="1 - 262" refId="ref43541" refString="Ramil, F. &amp; Vervoort, W. (1992) Report on the Hydroida collected by the &quot; BALGIM &quot; expedition in and around the Strait of Gibraltar. Zoologische Verhandelingen, Leiden, 277, 1 - 262." type="journal article" year="1992">Ramil &amp; Vervoort 1992</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bouillon, J. &amp; Gravili, C. &amp; Pages, F. &amp; Gili, J. M. &amp; Boero, F." box="[151,378,403,430]" pageId="8" pageNumber="420" refId="ref37985" refString="Bouillon, J., Gravili, C., Pages, F., Gili, J. M. &amp; Boero, F. (2006) An introduction to Hydrozoa. Editions du Museum, Paris, 591 pp." type="book" year="2006">
Bouillon 
<emphasis box="[255,311,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="420">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
). In West Africa, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Ramil &amp; Vervoort" authorityYear="1992" box="[569,677,403,429]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Bougainvilliidae" genus="Garveia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="8" pageNumber="420" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="nutans">
<emphasis box="[569,677,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="420">G. nutans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was only collected from 
<collectingCountry box="[957,1080,403,429]" name="Mauritania" pageId="8" pageNumber="420">Mauritania</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gil, M. &amp; Ramil, F." box="[1094,1313,403,429]" pageId="8" pageNumber="420" pagination="419 - 444" refId="ref39805" refString="Gil, M. &amp; Ramil, F. (2017 a) Hydrozoans from Mauritanian Deep-Waters. In: Ramos, A., Ramil, F. &amp; Sanz, J. L. (Eds.), Deep sea ecosystems off Mauritania: Researching marine biodiversity and habitats in West African Deep-waters. Springer, Dordrecht, pp. 419 - 444. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 024 - 1023 - 5 _ 11" type="book chapter" year="2017">Gil &amp; Ramil 2017a</bibRefCitation>
). Its bathymetric range stretches from 0 (
<bibRefCitation author="Schuchert, P." box="[494,674,439,465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="420" pagination="195 - 396" refId="ref44822" refString="Schuchert, P. (2007) The European athecate hydroids and their medusa (Hydrozoa, Cnidaria): Filifera Part 2. Revue suisse de Zoologie, 114, 195 - 396. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 80395" type="journal article" year="2007">Schuchert 2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuchert, P." box="[685,743,439,465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="420" pagination="1 - 364" refId="ref44871" refString="Schuchert, P. (2012) North-West European Athecate Hydroids and their Medusae. Synopses of the British Fauna, New Series, 59, 1 - 364." type="journal article" year="2012">2012</bibRefCitation>
) to 
<quantity box="[786,871,439,465]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.339" pageId="8" pageNumber="420" unit="m" value="1339.0">1339 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gil, M. &amp; Ramil, F." box="[885,1107,439,465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="420" pagination="419 - 444" refId="ref39805" refString="Gil, M. &amp; Ramil, F. (2017 a) Hydrozoans from Mauritanian Deep-Waters. In: Ramos, A., Ramil, F. &amp; Sanz, J. L. (Eds.), Deep sea ecosystems off Mauritania: Researching marine biodiversity and habitats in West African Deep-waters. Springer, Dordrecht, pp. 419 - 444. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 024 - 1023 - 5 _ 11" type="book chapter" year="2017">Gil &amp; Ramil 2017a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,501]" box="[199,835,475,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="420">
Our material was collected from depths of 
<quantity box="[679,831,475,501]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.62" metricValueMax="6.4" metricValueMin="4.84" pageId="8" pageNumber="420" unit="m" value="562.0" valueMax="640.0" valueMin="484.0">484 to 640 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
